Nokia smartphones have started receiving Android 8.0, stated HMD Global. The company said Android 8.0 Oreo is being introduced across its range of smartphones “as it was intended – in its purest form”. “Monthly software updates and bloat-free devices mean your Nokia phone will remain pure, secure, and up to date,” said Shaun Durandt, General Manager Southern Africa at HMD Global. “We are committed to giving Nokia fans the most pure, secure, and up-to-date Android experience, and are currently working on rolling out Android Oreo across our range of smartphones.”